        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer1967110336" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer16348686840270854431">According to the list at the back of this book I am culturally French. Who knew?<br/><br/>An odd and interesting little book on Food, the French way of life, and the secrets of French women. The major secret appears to be &quot;Don&apos;t feel guilty about what you eat.&quot; This is something I can live with.<br/><br/>There are a few interesting recipes scattered throughout the book, which the author cannot appear to decide whether it is a lifestyle book, cookbook, or personal memoir.<br/><br/>Makes for an interesting read.<br/><br/>Recommended.</span>
  <span id="freeText16348686840270854431" style="display:none">According to the list at the back of this book I am culturally French. Who knew?<br /><br />An odd and interesting little book on Food, the French way of life, and the secrets of French women. The major secret appears to be "Don't feel guilty about what you eat." This is something I can live with.<br /><br />There are a few interesting recipes scattered throughout the book, which the author cannot appear to decide whether it is a lifestyle book, cookbook, or personal memoir.<br /><br />Makes for an interesting read.<br /><br />Recommended.</span>
