<div id="review_19207899" class="review nosyndicate" itemprop="reviews" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Review">
  <link itemprop="url" href="https://www.goodreads.com/review/show/19207899" />
    <a title="Biz" class="left imgcol" href="/user/show/1044410-biz"><img alt="Biz" src="https://images.gr-assets.com/users/1207056301p2/1044410.jpg" /></a>

  <div class="left bodycol">
    <div class="reviewHeader uitext stacked">
        <a class="reviewDate createdAt right" href="/review/show/19207899?book_show_action=true">Apr 01, 2008</a>

      <span itemprop="author" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Person">
        <a title="Biz" class="user" itemprop="url" name="Biz" href="/user/show/1044410-biz">Biz</a>
      </span>

        rated it
        <span class=" staticStars notranslate" title="it was ok"><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10">it was ok</span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p0"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p0"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p0"></span></span>



        

          <div class="uitext greyText bookshelves">
            Shelves:
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/1044410-biz?shelf=read-food-and-nutrition">read-food-and-nutrition</a>
          </div>
    </div>


        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer19207899" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer8575773906259956646">This book is a mostly common sense based &quot;guide&quot; by someone with no background in nutrition. Many ideas are great- starting the day with a glass of water instead of sugary juices, for example, make a lot of sense and are great for one&apos;s skin. Walking more and taking the stairs? Also good. Some of the recipes are SUPER delicious (ie Ratatouille). Not sure if advising an entire weekend of nothing but &quot;magical&quot; leek soup is sound advice- there&apos;s not much magical about boiling leeks, even if tastes </span>
  <span id="freeText8575773906259956646" style="display:none">This book is a mostly common sense based "guide" by someone with no background in nutrition. Many ideas are great- starting the day with a glass of water instead of sugary juices, for example, make a lot of sense and are great for one's skin. Walking more and taking the stairs? Also good. Some of the recipes are SUPER delicious (ie Ratatouille). Not sure if advising an entire weekend of nothing but "magical" leek soup is sound advice- there's not much magical about boiling leeks, even if tastes good. Still, if you are looking to lose weight, her instructions to keep a food diary for a few weeks is surely a good place to start.</span>
  <a data-text-id="8575773906259956646" href="#" onclick="swapContent($(this));; return false;">...more</a>

          </span>
        </div>


